Code Description
200

This and all other 20x HTTP codes will be treated as successful operation (webhook dispatch will not be retried).

5XX

This, and all other HTTP codes, will be treated as a failure of hook receipt and NatWest will retry, with backoff, over a period of ~4.5 hours: exponentially starting 2min, 4min, 8min, 16min, 32min, 64min and 128 min.
When all the retries are exhausted, the webhooks that failed to be delivered to your endpoint will be held at NatWest in error status for up to 5 days and can be polled using 'https://api.natwest.com/event-subscriptions/v3.1/events/resend' endpoint.The failed webhooks can be polled during the retry period and successful pull will automatically stop retry of the webhook

Payment Status Enquiry

GET​/bankline-direct-digital​/commercial​/v1​/payment-status​/{transactionId}
Get the PAIN002 status message for a specific payment using unique transaction identifier


Oauth bearer token used for calling this endpoint must have scope "commercial-payments"

- You can use ‘Get Payment Status API’ to pull status messages that failed as webhooks or you can use it to get another copy of the PAIN02 status message.
The following special Characters ' / - . space are accepted in payment message for PSN Enquiry. If transaction id contains / then you must use query Param. The remaining special characters are supported by both query and Path Param.
- Path Param: GET https://api.natwest.com/bankline-direct-digital/commercial/v1/payment-status/rzVIHm2jCFHTymOKqx
- Query Param: GET https://api.natwest.com/bankline-direct-digital/commercial/v1/payment-status?transactionId=rzVIHm2jCFHTymOKqx.
Current Data retention period is 30 days and hence payment status upto 30 days old will be available to be pulled via this API.

Parameters

Name Description
transactionId *
integer
(path)

Your own Payment Reference, as submitted with the original payment in field 'CstmrCdtTrfInitn.PmtInf.CdtTrfTxInf.PmtId.InstrId' or 'CstmrCdtTrfInitn.PmtInf.PmtInfId'
- As mentioned in the Payment swagger specifications, TransactionId provided in the payment will be truncated if it exceeds 16 characters. Hence for the status enquiry to work as expected, please refrain from using TransactionId with more than 16 characters in the payment file.
- Status enquiry might show unexpected behaviour for TransactionId length exceeding 16 characters.

Example : abcdef12345678
